This paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of statistical learning for sentiment prediction, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.AI) and data mining (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of data and the creation of a dataset, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
